Key Match Events: Namibia needed a comfortable 18 runs to win off 18 balls but couldn't do it.
Mehran Khan delivered a wicket maiden to start a streak of 18 deliveries that almost turned the tables on Namibia to result in a Super Over.
Wiese hit a six to clear wide long on, just clearing the boundary.
Frylinck was run out in the final over, leaving Namibia needing 5 runs off 4 balls.
The match ended in a tie, resulting in a Super Over.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was part of the ICC Men's T20 World Cup.
